{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Broad post-rebase run completed 6948 passed / 58 skipped and exposed three late semantic integration gaps: exhaustive threshold routing omitted the new prerequisite-consistency criterion, its blocking-set pin still assumed the pre-feature set, and precheck schema additions had accidentally become required despite the existing backward-compatibility contract. All three existing RED oracles were remediated; focused regression set is 26 passed and make check is GREEN. A teardown guard error was diagnostic-only: HEAD changed because the commit was amended during the run. Final patchset commit f4dc5cf17 pushed to Gerrit 899; a clean broad rerun will run with HEAD held fixed."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784755449191814001,"uuid":"e19183d9-f2f4-4ad1-915c-8bd44bb94a86"}